### 4.4.2 Fixed-Point Convergence with Safety

The monad $T$ models iterative meta-cognitive processing. We prove convergence to a fixed point that preserves safety.

**Definition 4.4.1 (Scott-Continuity with Safety).** A functor $T: \mathbf{CR} \to \mathbf{CR}$ is Scott-continuous if it preserves colimits of $\omega$-chains, and for each chain $C_0 \to C_1 \to \cdots$, the safety witnesses $I(C_i) \to I(C_{i+1})$ compose to a witness $I(\text{colim } C_i)$.

