$$\text{fix}(T) = \bigsqcup_{n \in \mathbb{N}} T^n(\bot), \quad I(\text{fix}(T)).$$

*Proof.* The standard Kleene fixed-point theorem constructs $\text{fix}(T)$ as the colimit of the chain $\bot \to T(\bot) \to T^2(\bot) \to \cdots$. Scott-continuity ensures this colimit is a fixed point. The safety witnesses for each step compose to a witness for the colimit, proving $I(\text{fix}(T))$. ∎

